  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 3 is the close-out of the production-fix arc (Phases 1-3). After this gate, the project moves into Phase 4 (5 parallel quality-lift tracks: PCF audit / Stryker pilot / TestClock PoC / Coverlet baseline / anti-drift report) per spec.md FR-11..FR-14 and design.md §5.5.

      This exit gate is the LAST checkpoint where a Phase 1-3 regression can surface before Phase 4 begins. Any deterministic failure here triggers a Phase 3 reopen — Phase 4 cannot start with open production-fix gaps.

      Note: the final 6-TRX combined triple-run validation happens at Phase 5 close per FR-15. This Phase 3 exit is intentionally lighter (1 unit run today + cross-reference task 038's 3 integration runs) since Phase 4 is non-`src/`-modifying for tracks A, B, E and only modestly modifies for tracks C and D.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="038" status="must-be-complete">Spe.Integration.Tests triple-run produced 3 TRX with `Failed: 0`</dependency>
      <dependency task="030-037" status="must-be-complete">All 8 LOW severity production fixes complete with ledger entries → `repaired`</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
